          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Scattered photons were measured by four 60%",
                "HPGe detectors which were on average of 12 cm from",
                "the target, at a scattering angle of 120deg, with two",
                "in the horizontal plane, and two in the vertical",
                "plane. They were shielded with 2.5-cm Pb on the",
                "sides, and Pb (0.55 cm) and Cu (0.4 cm) filters were",
                "placed in front of the detectors to reduce the",
                "intensity of low energy photons hitting the detector."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "LCS"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A circular polarized gamma-ray beam was produced",
                "by Compton backscattering of laser photons from",
                "relativistic electrons in a storage ring. The levels",
                "were simultaneously excited by NRF using the high-flux",
                "of 1E+8 photons/s circularly polarized",
                "quasimonoenergetic gamma-ray beam"
              ]
            }
